Class TerminalEventListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.stripe.example.TerminalEventListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TerminalListener

    public class TerminalEventListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements TerminalListener
    The TerminalEventListener implements the TerminalListener interface and will forward along any events to other parts of the app that register for updates.

      • onUnexpectedReaderDisconnect

        public void onUnexpectedReaderDisconnect(Reader reader)
        Description copied from interface: TerminalListener
        The Terminal disconnected unexpectedly from the reader. In your implementation of this method, you may want to notify your user that the reader disconnected. You may also call Terminal.discoverReaders(com.stripe.stripeterminal.DiscoveryConfiguration, com.stripe.stripeterminal.DiscoveryListener, com.stripe.stripeterminal.Callback) to begin scanning for readers, and attempt to automatically reconnect to the disconnected reader. Be sure to either set a timeout or make it possible to cancel calls to Terminal.discoverReaders(com.stripe.stripeterminal.DiscoveryConfiguration, com.stripe.stripeterminal.DiscoveryListener, com.stripe.stripeterminal.Callback)
        Specified by:
        onUnexpectedReaderDisconnect in interface TerminalListener
        Parameters:
        reader - The previously connected reader.

      • onConnectionStatusChange

        public void onConnectionStatusChange(ConnectionStatus status)
        Description copied from interface: TerminalListener
        The Terminal's connection status changed. Note: You should *not* use this method to detect when a reader unexpectedly disconnects from your app, as it cannot be used to accurately distinguish between expected and unexpected disconnect events. To detect unexpect disconnects (e.g. to automatically notify your user), you should instead use the TerminalListener.onUnexpectedReaderDisconnect(com.stripe.stripeterminal.Reader) method.
        Specified by:
        onConnectionStatusChange in interface TerminalListener
        Parameters:
        status - The terminal's new connection status.
